    <div class="container">
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-md-12 col-lg-9"><p class="ff3" style="font-size:22px;">After a DeepWalk GNN is trained, the model has learned a good representation of each node as shown in the following figure. Different colors indicate different labels in the input graph. We can see that in the output graph (embedding with 2 dimensions), nodes having the same labels are clustered together, while most nodes with different labels are separated properly.</p></div></div></div></section><section data-bs-version="5.1" class="image3 cid-tt612oXwA9" id="image3-5" style="padding-top:0px; padding-bottom:0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">
